He has lived with pleasure, with envy, with the travail of loneliness, depression, and confusion. He has lived with great sorrow and with what he calls love, and with the everlasting fear of death. All this is his consciousness, which is common to all mankind. Realise what it means. It means that you are no longer an individual. This is very hard to accept because we have been programmed, as is the computer, to think we are individuals. We have been programmed religiously to think that we have souls separate from all the others. Being programmed, our brains work in the same pattern century after century.

Some languages-related thoughts:
Speaking/learning more than language at the same time may be funny but also hard sometimes. Of course, you may compare the languages you learn and tell the differences between them which help you understand and remember some rules or words.
But there are a lot of buts. Firstly, you often forget words in one of the languages, even if it's your mother tongue. You may also mix languages - I regularly mix Italian and German, mostly using Italian conjunctions while speaking German (don't know why xd). 
Also, when I speak more than one foreign language during the same day , my mind seems not to notice than I've changed a language I speak and insist on speaking in the previous one e.g. during German lesson I speak German but I have in my mind the phrases and sentences in Italian.
On the other hand, my mind sometimes accepts the change of a language too quickly e.g. I speak Italian but need to say sth in English and then find it so hard to start speaking Italian again ğŸ˜…
That's crazy ğŸ˜‚ and hard, sometimes ...
